<h2>Questions About Washer and Dryer Installation Cost</h2>

<h3>How much does washer and dryer installation cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>$220–300 for both units together — one trip, all connections made and tested, full cycle run, packaging hauled away. Dryer only: $150–200. Washer only: $150–200. Stacked configuration adds $50–75. Old unit removal $50–75 per unit.</p>

<h3>Do you install both gas and electric dryers?</h3>
<p>Yes. Electric: we confirm your outlet configuration before arriving (3-prong vs 4-prong) and bring both cord types. Gas: flexible connector to supply shutoff, soap solution leak test on every fitting after connection. If the existing flex connector is over 5 years old or kinked, we replace it — we carry connectors on the truck.</p>

<h3>What if the existing dryer vent duct needs work?</h3>
<p>We check the duct before connecting. If it's clogged, we can clean it same visit ($150–200). If it needs replacement, we quote separately ($149–450 depending on run length). We won't connect a new dryer to a problem duct — it causes thermal fuse failure within months.</p>

<h3>Can you stack my LG DLGX and DLEX?</h3>
<p>If they're a compatible pair — yes. Requires LG stacking kit KSTK1 or KSTK2 depending on model year. Not all DLGX/DLEX combinations are compatible. Give us both model numbers when you call and we confirm before arriving. Add $50–75 to base installation price.</p>

<h3>Will the store installation void my LG warranty?</h3>
<p>It can. LG's warranty specifies installation requirements — incorrect vent installation, wrong power connection, or improper leveling can give LG grounds to deny warranty claims. We install to LG's specifications so your warranty stays intact. We've repaired new machines in Torrance and Long Beach with denied warranty claims from exactly this situation.</p>

<h3>Can you come today?</h3>
<p>Yes — call (323) 990-7550. Same-day installation service across Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County, typically 2–4 hours from your call.</p>

